      "writtenOn": "2017-04-24T14:44:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I disagree. We don’t want gratuitous delays in tests. One second is actually a really long time. It’s pretty bad if every test slept for a second, and this sleep makes it a real pain to run this test in a tight --gtest_repeat loop.\n\nYou can do this with a sleep that’s way, way shorter than a second.",
      "revId": "bf45ada33a432caf27bc795e6b55a10ca7cd9b70",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
